I remember reading a story on reddit, long ago. Some guy was supposed to see a girl he met online, at her home. He went to the address, in a bad neighborhood, in the bad part of town. He found her house easy, but walking to the door, he heard a weird sound coming from the garage.

It reminded me of my favorite part of Don Quixote, when him and Sancho were seized with horror through an entire night at the sounds of fulling-mill hammers at a waterfall. I have had something similar happen in a forest, hearing drum-like noise, primal instinct to leave and run.

I think he described it as a low buzzing, a very faint, hard-to-hear roaring, like a machine motor. I believe it was daytime, early afternoon. But he was seized by an absolute fear when hearing that noise, and ran away, blocked her, never stepped close to that part of town again.
